---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '@/components/PageHeader.astro';
import EmailSignup from '@/components/EmailSignup.tsx';
import { site } from '@/lib/site';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="About the Fair Food Pricing campaign — who runs it, what its position is, and how to get in touch."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Who and why"
    title="About this campaign"
    intro="A short, honest explainer. No mission statements, no founder photos."
  />

  <article class="container-prose prose prose-neutral [&_a]:text-primary max-w-none py-10">
    <h2>Who runs this</h2>
    <p>
      The site is published independently by <strong>{site.publisher.name}</strong>. You can email <a
        href={`mailto:${site.publisher.email}`}>{site.publisher.email}</a
      >. We have no party affiliation. We have no paid staff. We do not receive funding from any
      retailer, retail body or technology vendor.
    </p>

    <h2>Why this</h2>
    <p>
      Most political causes are reactive — we recognise a harm, then legislate after the fact.
      AI-driven personalised pricing of food is one of the rare moments where the harm is visible on
      the horizon, the hardware is being installed, but the practices it enables have not yet become
      normal. The window to draw the line in advance is open. It will not be open for long.
    </p>

    <h2>What you can do</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <a href="/find-your-mp">Write to your MP</a> — the single biggest lever for a Private Member’s
        Bill.
      </li>
      <li>
        Forward the <a href="/downloads">one-page summary</a> to any MP, peer or journalist you know.
      </li>
      <li>
        Share <a href="/the-evidence">the evidence page</a> with anyone who thinks this is overblown.
      </li>
      <li>Keep up to date via the email list below (low-volume, GDPR-clean).</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Endorsements</h2>
    <p>
      None yet. The campaign launched on <time datetime="2026-05-17">17 May 2026</time>. If you are
      an MP, charity, faith group, academic or trade body considering endorsement, please get in
      touch.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="container-prose border-rule border-t py-8">
    <h2 class="font-display text-h2 text-ink font-semibold">Stay in the loop</h2>
    <p class="text-ink/85 mt-3">
      Occasional updates as the Bill moves. GDPR-compliant — explicit consent, no marketing lists,
      no analytics.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <EmailSignup client:visible />
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
